<chapter>
  <header>
    <title>Comet Release Notes
    <prepared>Jakob Cederlund
    <docno>
    <date>2001-02-01
    <rev>
    <file>notes.sgml
  </header>
 
  <p>Notes for Comet

 <section><title>Comet</title>
    
    <section><title>Improvements and New Features</title>
      <list>
	<item>Generates Erlang wrapper modules from COM TypeLibs.</item>
	<item>More examples, better documentation.</item>
      </list>
    </section>
    
    <section><title>Fixed Bugs and Malfunctions</title>
      <p>
	Improved stability, now works as a port program too.
    </section>
 
    <section><title>Known Bugs and Problems</title>
      <p>
	No way to avoid context switches (in Win32) when calling
	COM-object. This might be addressed in future versions.
    </section>
  </section>
  
  <section><title>Comet 1.1</title>

    <p>
      New release.
    <p>
      Greatly improved everything.
    <p>
      Comet can now be run as a port program and/or a port driver. The
      same API works in both.
    <p>
      Now generates Erlang wrapper modules around COM objects and
      interfaces, using information in COM TypeLibs.
    <p>
      Examples include controlling Internet Explorer, using Excel and
      accessing data through ADO.
      
  </section>
  <section><title>Comet 1.0</title>

    <p>New application.
      
  </section>

</chapter>

